                    "value": "<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per round;</p>\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> The night parade dances with wild abandon, unintentionally striking nearby creatures. It deals damage to each adjacent creature (<span data-pf2-saving-throw=\"reflex\" data-pf2-traits=\"damaging-effect\" data-pf2-label=\"Wasshoi! Wasshoi! DC\" data-pf2-dc=\"41\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">basic Reflex</span> save), and any creature that fails its save is pushed 10 feet in any direction as the night parade bounces it overhead. The damage depends on the number of actions.</p>\n<p><span class=\"pf2-icon\">1</span> [[/r 1d10 + 7 # bludgeoning damage]]{1d10 + 7 bludgeoning damage}</p>\n<p><span class=\"pf2-icon\">2</span> [[/r 4d10 + 14 # bludgeoning damage]]{4d10 + 14 bludgeoning damage}</p>\n<p><span class=\"pf2-icon\">3</span>[[/r 6d10 + 14 # bludgeoning damage]]{6d10 + 14 bludgeoning damage}</p>"
